Deputy national women leader of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Hajiya Zainab Ibrahim, has promised to strengthen capacities and re-evaluate campaign strategies to ensure a landslide victory for the party in the forthcoming general elections. Zainab, in a statement on Saturday in Abuja, said the women would assist the newly elected presidential candidate of the APC, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, to implement his fantastic blue prints since his leadership style is what the nation needs now. While congratulating Tinubu  for emerging presidential flag bearer of APC,  the deputy national women leader described him as the real father of politics in Nigeria, noting that he has been recognised for his accomplishments and sacrifices for the sustenance of democracy in Nigeria.   One die, three injured as gunmen attack Plateau community     Nurse gets support after losing legs in Owo terror attack     Igweship throne tears Enugu community apart   She stated that Nigeria is tasty of Tinubu’s transformative leadership, adding that his legacies still stand tall. According to her: “This is well deserved victory. The dedication and ability that got you here will continue to serve you well as you move along your path. “Success is yours comes year 2023 general election. You have proven to be a lion that you are. Your pragmatism speaks volumes as we are pleased with your candidature. We will work tireless to make sure we have genuine governance.”